  "name": "Noxious Needler",
  "pfs": {
    "availability": "Standard",
    "subtype": "pfs",
    "type": "stat_block_section"
  },
  "schema_version": 1.4,
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Noxious Needler",
      "sections": [
        {
          "image": {
            "image": "Sidebar_5_TreasureAndRewards.png",
            "name": "Treasure and Rewards",
            "type": "image"
          },
          "name": "Alchemical Leftovers",
          "sidebar_heading": "Treasure and Rewards",
          "sidebar_type": "treasure_and_rewards",
          "sources": [
            {
              "errata": {
                "alt": "1.1",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "1.1",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "link": {
                "alt": "Monster Core pg. 242",
                "aonid": 221,
                "game-obj": "Sources",
                "name": "Monster Core pg. 242",
                "type": "link"
              },
              "name": "Monster Core",
              "page": 242,
              "type": "source"
            }
          ],
          "subtype": "sidebar",
          "text": "When a noxious needler is defeated or disabled, each of its alchemical chambers that remains intact can be salvaged. The alchemical fluids inside are 50 gp worth of ingredients for crafting alchemical items.",
          "type": "section"
        }
      ],
      "sources": [
        {
          "errata": {
            "alt": "1.1",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "1.1",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "link": {
            "alt": "Monster Core pg. 242",
            "aonid": 221,
            "game-obj": "Sources",
            "name": "Monster Core pg. 242",
            "type": "link"
          },
          "name": "Monster Core",
          "page": 242,
          "type": "source"
        }
      ],
      "text": "This construct is a walking alchemical nightmare capable of inflicting all manner of painful wounds. The noxious needlers' ability to follow orders is granted by the otherwise mindless humanoid brain that floats in their dome-like heads, allowing them to serve as laborers and guards for their creators.  \n  \n In exceptionally rare cases, the brain used in their creation might retain fragments of memories or even an actual intellect, resulting in a noxious needler with a personality and agenda of its own. Unwilling creations often hunt down their creators, venting their rage on similar targets if revenge is impossible. Others blankly replicate the experiments from their last memory.",
      "type": "section"
    }
  ],
  "sources": [
    {
